commit.message:
Bump setup.py version to 2.0.2

Since I already tagged 2.0.1 but forgot to bump the version here, bumping it to
2.0.2 to re-tag for the actual upload.

Fix over-escaping in values

Fixes #20. In the 2.0 refactoring values were mistakenly changed to use key escaping. Since keys are more aggressively escaped the results would still decode correctly, but led to extra unnecessary escaping of whitespace in the value.

Fix Travis build

Remove old pip option.
Add Python 3.5 and 3.6 test configs.
Add setup.cfg for packaging
Document comments support
Add a type for COMMENT sentinel

Bump to version 2.0

Updating to 2.0 for the new file encoding support. Also moves the documentation
into the README for easier updates.

Support text-mode files for other encodings

Converts most of the inner workings to use text strings instead of byte strings.
Moves encoding to the outer layer so that if the file appears to have been
opened with an encoding (e.g. io.TextIOBase or similar) it will rely on the
existing encoding support. Files in bytes mode will continue to use the
"latin-1" encoding as specified in the Java documentation.
Bump tox Python 3 version to 3.6
Add .tox and .cache to .gitignore

Run functional tests against Java implementation

Converts the functional tests to use JPype to run the actual Java
implementation. This will prevent accidentally adding incorrect test
expectations based on a misreading of the spec.

The tests are also run against wrappers to pyjavaproperties and
python-jproperties to compare their implementations. These tests are marked as
xfail so that failures will just be reported, but not considered a failure for
the test run.

Add functional tests

Convert the unit tests for internal functions into functional tests of the
high-level API.

Also found and fixed an encoding issue when the value contains only whitespace.
Convert tests to use py.test

Enable iter_properties() to also yield comments

Adds a `comments` parameter to indicate that comments should be included. They
will contain the sentinel value `jprops.COMMENT` in place of the key.

Add LICENSE file

Add simplified 2-clause BSD license.

Fixes #10 and #11

Remove unneeded "test-requirements.txt" file

Requirements are now handled by Tox, so this isn't needed.
Point Travis CI config to use Tox
Bump to 1.0

Merge pull request #9 from mgood/feature/python3

Support for Python 3
Support for Python 3
Throw a better error when a key or value is not a string
Bump to version 0.2
Handle files with Windows or Mac line endings
Set up Travis CI
Ignore .DS_Store
Point setup.py "url" to the docs
Oops, forgot to add tests
Initial version
